#!/usr/bin/env bash
# SessionStart hook for neo-dev-toolkit plugin.
# Injects a reminder so Claude proactively invokes the bundled skills
# (neo-team, brainstorm, improve, api-doc-gen, confluence-api-doc, gitlab, commit)
# whenever a user request matches their triggering contexts.

set -euo pipefail

# Escape a string for safe embedding inside a JSON string literal.
# Uses bash parameter substitution for speed (single C-level pass per rule).
escape_for_json() {
    local s="$1"
    s="${s//\\/\\\\}"
    s="${s//\"/\\\"}"
    s="${s//$'\n'/\\n}"
    s="${s//$'\r'/\\r}"
    s="${s//$'\t'/\\t}"
    printf '%s' "$s"
}

session_context="<EXTREMELY_IMPORTANT>
You have the neo-dev-toolkit plugin installed. It bundles seven skills — invoke them via the Skill tool whenever the user's request matches.

1. **\`neo-team\`** — Orchestrate a specialist agent team (BA, Architect, Developer, QA, Code Reviewer, Security, System Analyzer). Use whenever a request has more than one software-development concern: new feature, multi-file bug fix, non-trivial PR/MR review, cross-module refactor. The skill is an ORCHESTRATOR — do not implement multi-concern work yourself. Delegate via the \`Agent\` tool following the skill's Delegation Protocol. Users can also launch it with \`/neo\`.

2. **\`brainstorm\`** — ALWAYS use before answering brainstorming, ideation, prompt-crafting, or open-ended exploration (\"brainstorm\", \"ช่วยคิด\", \"I have an idea\", \"improve this prompt\", \"let's explore\", \"I want to build\"). Transforms vague requests into actionable outputs via adaptive guided questioning.

3. **\`improve\`** — Iteratively improve any output (code, prose, data, config) until measurable criteria are met. Triggers: \"improve this\", \"make it better\", \"iterate\", \"refine\", \"ปรับปรุง\", \"ทำให้ดีขึ้น\".

4. **\`api-doc-gen\`** — Generate or validate API docs from source. Triggers: \"gen api doc\", \"สร้าง api doc\", \"อัปเดต api doc\", \"document these endpoints\", \"api doc outdated\".

5. **\`confluence-api-doc\`** — Sync docs/api/ to Confluence pages via acli + REST. Triggers: \"sync api doc\", \"push doc to confluence\", \"อัปเดต api doc ไป confluence\".

6. **\`gitlab\`** — Interact with GitLab via the \`glab\` CLI (create / update / read / review / fix / CI fix / feedback for MRs). Triggers: any GitLab MR URL, \"สร้าง MR\", \"review MR\", \"fix CI\", \"แก้ pipeline\", \"แก้ตาม comment\".

7. **\`commit\`** — Smart git commit workflow with protected-branch guard, rebase onto base, secret-aware staging, and conventional commit messages. ALWAYS use this skill whenever the user asks to commit — do not run \`git commit\` directly. Triggers: \"commit\", \"/commit\", \"commit changes\", \"save my work\", \"push this\", \"commit and push\", \"commit ให้หน่อย\", \"ช่วย commit\", \"เสร็จแล้ว\", \"save and push\".

Single-file fixes, quick questions, and pure research tasks do NOT need these skills — answer directly.
</EXTREMELY_IMPORTANT>"

context_escaped=$(escape_for_json "$session_context")

# Emit only the shape the current platform consumes.
# - Cursor:   additional_context (top-level, snake_case)
# - Claude Code: hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext (nested)
# - Copilot CLI / SDK standard: additionalContext (top-level, camelCase)
if [ -n "${CURSOR_PLUGIN_ROOT:-}" ]; then
  printf '{\n  "additional_context": "%s"\n}\n' "$context_escaped"
elif [ -n "${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT:-}" ] && [ -z "${COPILOT_CLI:-}" ]; then
  printf '{\n  "hookSpecificOutput": {\n    "hookEventName": "SessionStart",\n    "additionalContext": "%s"\n  }\n}\n' "$context_escaped"
else
  printf '{\n  "additionalContext": "%s"\n}\n' "$context_escaped"
fi

exit 0
